Implementation details for background services integration:

## Architecture Changes
- main.go now manages lifecycle of CleanupService and CostMonitor
- Shared state.Store instance used across providers and services
- Context cancellation propagates to all background services

## New CLI Flags
- -enable-cost-monitor: Enable AWS Cost Explorer integration
- -enable-auto-teardown: Enable automatic teardown when budget exceeded

## Graceful Shutdown
- Signal handling for SIGINT/SIGTERM
- CleanupService.Stop() waits for current cleanup to complete
- CostMonitor.Stop() waits for current check to complete
- HTTP server uses graceful Close() instead of immediate shutdown

## Logging Migration
- cleanup.go: log.Printf → logging.WithComponent + slog methods
- monitor.go: log.Printf → logging.WithComponent + slog methods
- Consistent structured logging across all services

## Why This Matters
- CleanupService was implemented but never started - expired plans accumulated
- CostMonitor was implemented but never started - no runtime cost enforcement
- Now both services run automatically when server starts
- Cost monitoring is opt-in via flag to avoid AWS API calls when not needed
